om co-planar orbits, low\neccentricities ($e=0.05$), and planet masses equal to the minimum mass derived\nfrom the best-fit circular orbit fitting. Besides, the planets are not likely\nin mean motion resonance. HD 184010 system is unique: it is the first system\ndiscovered to have a highly evolved star ($\\log g < 3.5$ cgs) and more than two\ngiant planets all with intermediate orbital periods ($10^2\\ \\rm{d} < P < 10^3\\\n\\rm{d}$).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Sep 2022 02:50:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-21"}
